  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean package)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors scoped-out (acceptable at MRL 2). One explicitly-flagged uncertainty gap in the discretization error factor is documented with full rationale and accepted as residual risk consistent with MRL 2 requirements. Decision: Accepted.",
