      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/discretization-gci-6pct-threshold",
      "rationale": "Three-level GCI study conducted on systematically refined meshes (2.1M, 5.8M, 14.2M cells). GCI fine-grid uncertainty on hemolysis index: 6.8%. EXPLICITLY FLAGGED LIMITATION: the asymptotic range condition (GCI ratio = 0.97) is marginally outside the ideal band, indicating the solution is near but not fully in the asymptotic convergence regime. This gap is documented and quantified; the 6.8% bound is carried forward conservatively into RHI comparison. With this bound applied, worst-case RHI upper bound = 0.87, still satisfying RH < 1.0 acceptance criterion with margin of 0.13. The limitation is accepted as residual risk at MRL 2 given the demonstrated margin and the medium model influence designation. Achieved level 2 meets MRL 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/test-conditions-cpb-operating-envelope",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation data acquired at flow rates 2.0–6.0 L/min and speeds 2400–3200 RPM, spanning the full COU operating envelope of 5 flow-speed combinations. Temperature controlled at 37°C ±0.5°C consistent with CPB clinical conditions. Fluid viscosity matched to diluted blood (2.7 cP ±0.1 cP). Test conditions adequately represent COU boundary conditions at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-pressure-flow-mae",
      "rationale": "Pressure-flow curve predictions compared against FDA CDRH benchmark experimental data at 15 operating points across 3 speeds. Mean absolute error 4.2 mmHg (2.9% of full-scale range), within ±2 standard deviations of experimental scatter at all points. Quantitative agreement metric exceeds MRL 2 threshold. RHI output comparison against predicate device reference demonstrates RH = 0.81 (worst case), satisfying acceptance criterion with margin."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-rhi-hemolysis",
      "rationale": "Primary quantity of interest is the relative hemolysis index (RHI), which directly maps to the COU decision criterion (RH < 1.0 vs. predicate device). Secondary QoIs include shear stress distribution and residence time, both of which are inputs to the hemolysis power-law model (Giersiepen et al.). QoIs are directly relevant to the clinical endpoint of pump-induced hemolysis during CPB."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-fda-benchmark",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is the same geometry used in the COU. Operating conditions in validation experiments span the COU envelope. Blood analog fluid (glycerin-water, viscosity matched) used in experiments is appropriate for hemolysis model validation at MRL 2. The validation domain is sufficiently representative of the COU to support the credibility claim."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 with medium model influence, separate quantification of numerical solver error beyond code verification (MMS, level 3 achieved) is not required. The MMS study confirms second-order convergence and absence of systematic solver defects. Iterative convergence monitored to residual tolerance 1e-6 for all simulations. Scoped out per MRL 2 factor requirements table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal use error analysis not required at MRL 2. Analyst training records reviewed (two analysts with >5 years CFD experience in cardiovascular applications). Standard operating procedures for simulation setup, boundary condition assignment, and post-processing documented and followed. Peer review of simulation inputs completed by independent analyst. Scoped out per MRL 2 factor requirements table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal model form uncertainty quantification not required at MRL 2. Turbulence model sensitivity assessed qualitatively via k-omega SST vs. RSM comparison (±4.1% on peak hemolysis index), incorporated into combined uncertainty bound on RHI. Newtonian fluid assumption appropriate for high-shear CPB conditions (shear rates >100 s-1 throughout pump). Scoped out per MRL 2 factor requirements table."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-inputs-scoped-out-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Formal sensitivity analysis of all model inputs not required at MRL 2. Geometric inputs derived from FDA-published CAD files with dimensional tolerances ±0.05 mm. Fluid properties from ASTM standard reference data. Boundary conditions from clinical CPB operating specifications. Key input sensitivities (rotational speed ±50 RPM, flow rate ±0.2 L/min) assessed informally and found to produce <3% variation in RHI. Scoped out per MRL 2 factor requirements table."
    },
    {
